frameDefinitions: An Experiencer actualizes a certain pattern of behavior, a Lifestyle, which persists for a significant period of time in the Experiencer's life and is recognized as part of his character or normal routine.
This frame concerns transparent nouns that denote Instances of Types of entities or events.
A Protagonist is in the dynamic, maintained state of being alive or has exited this state.
An Agent changes Tools, from the Old_tool to a New_tool.
There exist a number of different possible Situations that may happen in the future.
An State_of_affairs will come to hold with respect to a Protagonist at some future time.
frameExamples: He <t>lived</t> a hedonistic life before he settled down.

The survey confirmed that management interference in team operations had increased , and <t><fex name='Instance'>instances</fex></t> of management decisions being taken without team consultation had also increased .
If this happens one more time, we 're going to <t>switch</t> operating systems.
You have but two <t><fex name='Situation'>choices</fex></t> for your daughter .
Exile was his <t>fate</t> and he triumphantly turned it into the fruit of his life.
listRoleDefinitions: The person who actualizes a pattern of behavior.
A pattern of behavior which the actions of the <fen>Experiencer</fen> matches for a significant period of time.
The <fen>Lifestyle</fen> may be characterized by a <fen>Manner</fen>, which is often expressed adverbially.
A temporal description of when the <fen>Experiencer</fen> adopts a <fen>Lifestyle</fen>.
The spatial location where the <fen>Experiencer</fen> carries out a <fen>Lifestyle</fen>.
A thing or episode of a certain <fen>Type</fen>.
The category of thing or event of which an <fen>Instance</fen> is picked out.
<fen>Protagonist</fen> identifies the being or entity that is  dead or alive.
This role identifies the <fen>Figure</fen> or form being described by the target.
The time in which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is dead or alive.
The individual that changes their situation.
The entities controlled by an Agent to achieve some Purpose.
The tool that the <fen>Agent</fen> had been using.
The tool that the <fen>Agent</fen> ends up using.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> acts intentionally.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> makes a change.
Something that may happen in the future, or at least whose factual status is unresolved. This is often tagged in a second role layer and generally contains the target.

An individual involved in the <fen>Event</fen>.

'<fex name='Agent'>You</fex> have a <t>choice</t>.'
An entity intimately involved in the <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> that is destined to occur to the Protagonist.
The Protagonist is the one for whom the future <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> is destined.
The <fen>Role</fen> filled by the <fen>Protagonist</fen> in his/her destiny.
The time for which the <fen>Protagonist</fen>'s future is determined.
The location in which <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> is destined to occur to the <fen>Protagonist</fen>.
listRoleExamples: He lived <fex>the life of a beggar</fex>.
I collected two <t>specimens</t> <fex>of this rare species</fex>.
You have one choice to make <fex>for him</fex>.
Deciding that his true destiny is <fex>as a healer</fex>, Henderson returns home, planning to enter medical school.
Their destiny <fex>over those years</fex> was to gradually take charge of most of the world's operations.
